@Lewis, a joy to see your name!  The news videos can't really communicate all of what Helene survivors are dealing with, and to hear that you are finding ways to help one another cope with such chaos and ruin is inspiring. The loss must be hard enough to face, but the day-to-day ordeal of finding water, food, and shelter for everyone while starting to clean up the destruction sounds exhausting.  

Good for you that you have kept your love of life and are in the thick of reclaiming your beautiful town.  We are holding your place at the table and looking forward to having your rich and insightful comments again.

Be well, be safe, and thank you for finding the time to let us hear from you.

