@DocP - TUDE is a word, whether you like it or not. It is a slangy way to say "attitude" and I have been hearing it for years.

Slang is allowed in these puzzles. So are words that you, personally, do not like. So are words that I, personally, do not like. I just don't whine about the ones I don't like when they appear in the puzzle. (Although, I have to admit, I do comment on the execrable plural of "octopus" whenever it appears, although I always end my screed with the statement that, even though I do not like it, and would never use it, it is OK for a puzzle to include it.)

STUNTS and TUDE are "better" Thant STiNTS and TiDE because they actually answer the clues, whereas your two suggestions do not, even remotely, answer the clues. They are also the answers, which sort of counts.
